entry.title: Webview suppress tap during fling
entry.content:
For apps that disables fling in webview by not calling computeScroll,

webview still internally has a fling curve that's just not ticked. This

caused crbug.com/514783 for those apps because tap during fling cancels

the fling instead of registering as a tap. The old fix was to turn off

this tap suppression during fling entirely, which causes this current

bug where apps that allow normal fling will have tap register as a tap,

which differs from chrome behavior.



This changes so that fling is cancelled entirely for apps that do not

call computeScroll, but keeps tap suppression behavior.

entry.title: [Downloads] Consolidate and fix Download.ShowedDownloadWarning logging
entry.content:
Previously we only logged to this histogram when a download warning was

shown in the download bubble, a notification, or the obsolete download

shelf. Given that the download bubble is suppressed for 15s after it is

shown, it is possible for a dangerous download warning to occur but not

be shown in the download bubble. Later on, the user could go to

chrome://downloads and be shown the warning, but this wouldn't be logged

to the histogram. This causes the histogram count to be lower than the

actual number of warnings shown to the user.



This CL fixes that by logging from chrome://downloads as well. We ensure

that each warning is only logged once by checking and setting the

WasUIWarningShown bit on the DownloadItemModel.



Since the missing warnings from chrome://downloads are expected to be

a low number, we do not change the name of the histogram. This histogram

is particularly costly to rename because it contains many years of

historical data and is used to populate internal dashboards.



Also some drive-by fixes.

entry.title: [ios] Fix for MagicStack / module layout guide unsatisfiable constraints
entry.content:
When creating and attempting to insert MagicStack modules before the

MagicStack itself has been created (and before the MagicStack module

layout guide has been created), the module would end up with a width

constraint equal to zero. Later when the MagicStack is created the

modules are inserted and a proper width constraint is added which

conflicts with the previously added bad constraint. This change prevents

a width constraint from being added before the MagicStack is

instantiated, and makes it clear that the module wont really be inserted

before then.

entry.title: Allow calc() values in xywh/rect
entry.content:
This patch fixes two checks that are hit when using calc() in xywh/rect

values:

1. We cannot check for non-negative calc expressions at parse time in

the general case (see: `GetDoubleValue()` in css_primitive_value.h),

so this patch makes the DCHECK only apply to numeric literals.

cannot guarantee ranges in CalculationValue::Add. This is used when

computing the inset value of xywh/rect (see:

https://drafts.csswg.org/css-shapes/#basic-shape-computed-values),

where the w and h values are non-negative, but the x and y values

can be anything.

entry.title: Record histograms for LCP of non-tab WebUI content
entry.content:
This CL adds some histograms to record the Time to Largest Contentful Paint of different WebUI surfaces. To achieve this, it introduces a new `PageLoadMetricsObserver` subclass that is only installed for `WebContents` associated with a `BubbleContentsWrapperT`. This should cover all of side-panel WebUI contents, as well as some bubbles set up using this wrapper.

entry.title: [Signin] Fix race conditions in FakeAccountManagerFacade
entry.content:
FakeAccountManagerFacade allows reading/changing the list of accounts

from different threads. Prior to this CL, it was avoiding data races

by using a lock object. However, this was still incorrect from the

behavioral point of view - it meant that calling getCoreAccountInfos

multiple times from the same method on the main thread could produce

different results, which is not how it works in production.



This CL fixes the issue by replacing the lock object with checkUiThread

and runOnUiThreadBlocking - now mAccountHolders is only accessed on

the UI thread.
